sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant KServe as KServe Ingress<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant AuthMW as AuthenticationMiddleware<br/>API Key Validation
    participant API as OpenAI API Server<br/>8000/TCP HTTP
    participant Engine as AsyncLLM Engine (V1)<br/>PagedAttention
    participant Executor as Model Executor<br/>CPU (C/C++ kernels)
    participant HFHub as Hugging Face Hub<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over Engine,HFHub: Flow 2: Model Loading at Startup
    Engine->>HFHub: GET model weights + tokenizer<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (HF_TOKEN)<br/>TLS 1.2+
    HFHub-->>Engine: Model artifacts
    Engine->>Engine: Load model into CPU memory<br/>Initialize KV Cache

    Note over Client,Executor: Flow 1: Chat Completion Request
    Client->>KServe: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    KServe->>AuthMW: Forward request<br/>HTTP 8000/TCP
    AuthMW->>AuthMW: Validate API Key<br/>(VLLM_API_KEY)
    AuthMW->>API: Authenticated request
    API->>Engine: Submit inference request<br/>(async, in-process)
    Engine->>Executor: Execute model forward pass<br/>(in-process, Python/C++)
    Executor-->>Engine: Token logits
    Engine->>Engine: Sample tokens<br/>PagedAttention + Continuous Batching
    Engine-->>API: Generated tokens (streaming)
    API-->>KServe: SSE stream response<br/>HTTP chunked
    KServe-->>Client: JSON/SSE response<br/>HTTPS

    Note over Client,S3: Alternative: S3 Model Loading
    Engine->>S3: GET model via tensorizer<br/>Auth: AWS IAM (S3_ACCESS_KEY_ID)<br/>TLS 1.2+
    S3-->>Engine: Model artifacts
